<br>
The basic idea is to /pet attack the mob, and as soon as your pet casts his root, /pet back off him, so he returns to your side unscathed.  Then you nuke once or twice while the root holds, then send your pet back in to root once.<br>
<br>
So thus, your pet is the Yo-Yo. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nitrooftheorb>Nitro of the Orb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 260<br> <font color=#333333>(2/24/03 5:10:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=472.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Snare and Fear</span><hr size=1> Use a lumi orb and do reverse aggro kiting -- works fine. Speaking of which, anyone know when it's clickable? <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=361567">Draogan</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> -- 63 Archmage<br>
